6 AS INTRODUCED
7 An Act relating to marriage; amending 43 O.S. 2021,
Section 105, which relates to dissolution of
8 marriage; directing the Oklahoma Bar Association to
prepare standard forms; directing the Administrative
9 Office of the Courts to provide access to forms;
providing that standardized forms are not required;
10 and providing an effective date.
11
12
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
14 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 43 O.S. 2021, Section 105, is
15 amended to read as follows:
16 Section 105. A. A proceeding for dissolution of marriage, an
17 annulment of a marriage, or a legal separation shall be titled "In
18 re the Marriage of _______ and ______".
19 B. The initial pleading in all proceedings under this title
20 shall be denominated a petition. The person filing the petition
21 shall be called the petitioner. A responsive pleading shall be
22 denominated a response. The person filing the responsive pleading
23 shall be called the respondent. Other pleadings shall be
24
